ElderSense AI Code of Conduct
Our Pledge

In the interest of fostering an open and welcoming environment, we as contributors and maintainers pledge to make participation in ElderSense AI a harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of age, gender, experience level, or background.

Our Standards

Examples of behavior that contributes to a positive environment include:

Being respectful and considerate in all interactions.

Using welcoming and inclusive language.

Showing empathy, especially towards elderly users or those with limited digital literacy.

Constructive feedback and encouragement.

Examples of unacceptable behavior include:

Harassment, discrimination, or hate speech of any kind.

Public or private insults, personal attacks, or threats.

Sharing inappropriate content.

Disrespecting community decisions or intentionally sabotaging the project.

Enforcement

Project maintainers have the right and responsibility to remove comments, commits, or contributors that violate this Code of Conduct. Persistent or severe violations may lead to a temporary or permanent ban from the project.

Reporting

If you witness or experience unacceptable behavior, please report it to the maintainers at: [your email/contact link]. All reports will be handled confidentially.

Acknowledgment

By participating in ElderSense AI, you agree to abide by this Code of Conduct.
